    <text id="B0694T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo asks Tannehill to deduct the wages of his employee, Charles Brown, who is
                    accused of stealing certain items from a Joshua Harris.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF &amp;
                        AL</abbr> 4th <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9 <abbr expan="Sub District">Sub
                            Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Joseph F. <orig reg="Tannehill"
                        >Tannyhill</orig><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-10-22"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 22/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The bearer Joshua Harris (colored) complains to this office that <abbr
                        expan="Charles">Chas</abbr> Brown (colored) Employed by you is indebted to
                    him (<abbr expan="Harris">H</abbr>) to <abbr expan="amount">amt</abbr> of $
                        3.<hi rend="super">
                        <hi rend="underline">00</hi>
                    </hi> - One dollar being for shirt sold said Brown and $2<hi rend="underline">
                        <hi rend="super">00</hi>
                    </hi> for <unclear>
                        <abbr expan="pair">pr</abbr>
                    </unclear>sheets &amp; one <unclear>razor</unclear>which said Brown stole
                    from Harris nearly <unclear>two years</unclear> ago - which amount Brown
                    promised to pay Harris, he having acknowledged the theft <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> Brown
                    having continually baffled <unclear>Harris</unclear><del rend="none" hand="h1"/> the payment
                    of this debt, I most respectfully request that a sufficient amount <unclear>be
                        remitted</unclear> from Brown's wages to settle it.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="servant">sert</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo <unclear>
                            <abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">ASA Comr</abbr>
                        </unclear></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Mr. <orig reg="Tannehill">Tannyhill</orig> paid Harris
                            <abbr expan="amount">amt</abbr> $3.00 &amp; deducted same from wages
                        of Brown</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
